resources.retention_range_tooltip:
These points signify the duration for which you want to retain the recovery points. You may have any number of daily/weekly/monthly/yearly points retained for the duration you specify.

The default values have been computed using Azures telemetry data. You can either edit these fields or leave them at default values.
resources.average_daily_churn_tooltip:
Different workloads have different churn rates. While a File/Folder workload would usually have a low to moderate churn rate, an SQL database on the other hand would have a high churn rate. Typically the values are as follows -

  • Low (up to 2%)
  • Moderate (3%-4%)
  • High (5% and above)

The default value has been determined by the weighted average daily churn for your workload, computed using Azure's telemetry data. You can either edit this field or leave it at default value.
resources.average_frontend_data_size: Average front-end data size across each VM or Server.
resources.storage_cost_calculation_tooltip: Monthly storage costs increase over time due to growth in storage, and are directly proportional to workload churn, and retention range. Storage grows to a point beyond which it becomes steady, referred to as steady state
resources.choose_one_of: Choose one of the following options to see your storage cost estimates at different points in time.
